<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1735,1906]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,286,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Ploeogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,286,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Ploeogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently includes 10 valid species (
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado, J. C." box="[691,886,1735,1761]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" refId="ref13244" refString="Maldonado, J. C. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the World. Caribbean Journal of Science, Special publication No. 1. University of Puerto Rico, Mayaguez, 694 pp." type="book" year="1990">Maldonado 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[896,1195,1735,1761]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="91 - 99" refId="ref12042" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Webb, M. D. (2019) Transfer of the assassin bug Helonotus pallidulus Walker to the genus Heza Amyot &amp; Serville (Hemiptera, Heteroptera, Reduviidae, Harpactorinae, Harpactorini). ZooKeys, 872, 91 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 872.35137" type="journal article" year="2019">Gil-Santana &amp; Webb 2019</bibRefCitation>
), all in need of a revision, since only the information provided in the original descriptions, all of them published in the 19th century, are available for most of the species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[527,794,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Ploeogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mammosus">
<emphasis box="[527,794,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Ploeogaster mammosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from “Cayenne” (
<collectingCountry box="[1165,1335,1807,1834]" name="French Guiana" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." pageId="13" pageNumber="394" refId="ref10418" refString="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1843) Histoire naturelle des insects: Hemipteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret. Fain et Thunot, Paris, 675 pp., 12 pls." type="book" year="1843">Amyot &amp; Serville 1843</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<bibRefCitation author="Villiers, A." box="[428,593,1843,1869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="679 - 684" refId="ref13861" refString="Villiers, A. (1971) Reduviidae [Heteroptera] recoltes en Guyane Francaise par la mission du Museum National D'Histoire Naturelle. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, New Series, 7 (3), 679 - 684." type="journal article" year="1971">Villiers (1971)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned two additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1056,1191,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Ploeogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1191,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Ploeogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1432,1843,1869]" name="French Guiana" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, unidentified to species level. An additional species is recorded here.
</paragraph>
